<paragraph blockId="35.[151,530,654,681]" box="[151,530,654,681]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,654,681]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
11. Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1887" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[281,530,654,681]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,359,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Scaria</emphasis>
Bolívar, 1887
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,727,934]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
This genus was recently studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Mendes, D. M. M. &amp; Silva, D. S. M. &amp; Cardona Granda, J. M. &amp; Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J." box="[585,955,727,753]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1" refId="ref22188" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Mendes, D. M. M., Silva, D. S. M., Cardona Granda, J. M., Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J. (2019) Systematics and biogeography of the genus Scaria Bolivar, 1887 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Batrachideinae). Zootaxa, 4675 (1), 001 - 065. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4675.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cadena-Castañeda 
<emphasis box="[806,867,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
and is easily distinguish from the other batrachideines by slender body; antennae 20–22 segmented; anterior margin of the pronotum (lateral and dorsal view) hook-like (median carina sharply cristate); mid femur apical spine presence; wings present in all species; no brachypronotal form is known; presence of lateral darkish perpendicular band from eyes to disc pronotal region usually present (
<figureCitation box="[340,426,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 34. Scaria verutum (Grant, 1956) (holotype of Rehnidium verutum Grant, 1956) (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614462/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[574,647,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[574,647,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Scaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of 11 species in four species groups: 
<emphasis box="[1183,1267,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">hamata</emphasis>
group; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruner" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1358,1436,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Eutettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis box="[1358,1436,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">lineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group; 
<emphasis box="[231,287,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">laeta</emphasis>
group and 
<emphasis box="[414,514,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">producta</emphasis>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Mendes, D. M. M. &amp; Silva, D. S. M. &amp; Cardona Granda, J. M. &amp; Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J." box="[601,946,907,934]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1" refId="ref22188" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Mendes, D. M. M., Silva, D. S. M., Cardona Granda, J. M., Garcia, A. G. &amp; Tumbrinck, J. (2019) Systematics and biogeography of the genus Scaria Bolivar, 1887 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Batrachideinae). Zootaxa, 4675 (1), 001 - 065. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4675.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Cadena-Castañeda 
<emphasis box="[818,874,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
, 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[969,1053,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1651,1675]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1627]" captionTargetId="figure-134@49.[151,1436,561,1627]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 40. Map of approximated occurrence of the genus Scaria Bolívar, 1887." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614474" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614474/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
